  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I download torrents on my computer?",
  "response": "Downloading torrents involves several steps and requires specific software. Here's a general guide to follow:\n\n1. **Install a Torrent Client:**\n   - You'll need a torrent client to download files. Popular options include:\n     - **qBittorrent**: Lightweight and open-source.\n     - **Transmission**: Simple and efficient.\n     - **Vuze**: Feature-rich, but may be heavy on resources.\n     - **BitTorrent/\u03bcTorrent**: Widely used, but sometimes bundled with adware (opt for \u03bcTorrent Classic if using \u03bcTorrent).\n   - Download the client of your choice from its official website and follow the installation instructions.\n\n2. **Find a Torrent File or Magnet Link:**\n   - Torrents are typically found on torrent websites or search engines.\n   - **Torrent file**: A small file with a .torrent extension that you download and open with your torrent client.\n   - **Magnet link**: A hyperlink that directly opens in your torrent client; no separate file is downloaded.\n   - Be cautious of the sites you use to find torrents; choose reputable sources to avoid malware and copyright issues.\n\n3. **Open the Torrent File or Magnet Link:**\n   - If you have a torrent file, double-click it, or open it directly in your torrent client.\n   - For magnet links, clicking them should open your torrent client automatically if it's installed correctly.\n\n4. **Configure and Start the Download:**\n   - Once the torrent is added to your client, you can choose the download destination on your computer.\n   - The torrent client will begin downloading the file. Make sure your internet connection is stable.\n\n5. **Monitor the Download:**\n   - The client will show the progress and estimated time for completion.\n   - Be aware that upload (seeding) also occurs, which shares parts of the file with others.\n\n6. **Once Downloaded:**\n   - After completion, scan the downloaded files with antivirus software to ensure they're safe.\n   - You can choose to keep seeding (uploading) to help others, or stop the upload to save bandwidth.\n\n7. **Legal and Ethical Considerations:**\n   - Ensure the content you're downloading and sharing is legal in your jurisdiction.\n   - Respect copyright laws and consider the ethical implications of downloading certain content.\n\nRemember, downloading or sharing copyrighted material without permission may be illegal in your country, so always verify the legitimacy of the content you're downloading.",
